explanation: The solution uses a stack to parse the formula and count the atoms. It iterates through the formula, pushing new dictionaries onto the stack when it encounters an open parenthesis and popping them off when it encounters a close parenthesis. The counts are then multiplied by the multiplier after the close parenthesis and added to the counts in the previous dictionary. The final counts are then sorted and appended to the result string.

